@Goat******76 I agree with your take bar from the fact that you're disregarding Aaron Picos submission win against Aiden Lee, sure his record is rough but Aiden Lee does not suck lol he's a very crafty vet and he has been on a roll recently.

He's also fought tough opponents practically his whole career and has pretty good wins over fighters like Ludovit Klein, Lee is nasty on the ground majority of his losses came from SD and some Knockouts but subbing him is no joke at all its very impressive.

[Predictions]

@The Duck he doesn't deserve the credit for his win against Pantoja, but he does deserve the recognition as a champion despite the result, and the sheer fact that he's so active at such a young age and that 5 months before he had a 3 round war against the #1 contender at the time where they threw 200 significant strikes each is mindblowing.

