[Predictions]

@McFarlanders first of all there was no dirty move. It's no one's fault for what happened to Pantoja. Those things sometimes happen, and this time Pantoja was unlucky it had to happen to him. Going life and death with Royval doesn't mean he's not a very high level fighter, he clearly won that fight, but doesn't happen to have the KO power that Kape has, hence he wasn't able to KO Royval even though he hurt him multiple times throughout the fight and also dropped him in the last round. As you can see by my pfp I'm a major Manel Kape believer and I think he's the best 125er on the planet right now, but trying to undermine Joshua Van is a ******** move, even for an obvious ragebaiter like you.

